Data Persistence 

Types of Databases 

1. Structured Query Language (SQL) Databases/ Relational Databases
Ex: Oracle DB, MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQLite, & Cetera.


2. No Structured Query Language (No SQL) Databases 
Examples are MongoDB and Cassandra. These types of database use JSON-like documents instead of tables to store data.
Ex: MongoDB, Cassandra, HBase, Redis, Google BigTable, Amazon DynamoDB etc.

So, Vertically means having records, & horizontally means having fields.